Dean Elgar and Temba Bavuma at the Wanderers, Johannesburg. JOHANNESBURG - Quinton de Kock has been relieved of the burden of on-field leadership. Dean Elgar will replace him as test match captain. Significantly as well, Temba Bavuma will lead the limited-overs teams. READ: Patel, Ashwin spin England out for 205 in final Test He will become the first black African to captain the Proteas. Bavuma's leadership stock grew during the CSA T20 Challenge. He led the Lions to the T20 Challenge title and also batted well but leading the Proteas will come with much more scrutiny and pressure.